A teenager found dead inside his pick-up truck in January had overdosed on heroin and did not freeze to death as first thought. 

Police investigated the possibility 19-year-old Andrew Norris died from hypothermia after his frozen body was found outside his family's Ohio home in zero-degree temperatures on January 23.

However an autopsy conducted by Cuyahoga County Medical Examiner’s Office has now revealed the teen died from a drug overdose, The News Herald reported.

