Earlier this year, 19 Action News reported Norris's stepmother found his 
frigid body slumped in the front seat of his snow-covered vehicle in the driveway of their Erich Drive, Willoughby Hills home. 

Police said Norris's family had last seen him a few days before his death and believed he was staying with a friend.  

Police also said at the time there were no signs of violence, alcohol or drug activity in the 
vehicle and that it was difficult to see Norris in the car from the 
outside.

Detective Brian Jackson of Willoughby Police told the News-Herald: 'Whether he died because of the cold or not, we don’t know.'

